{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2cbb8f57-1b5b-466a-9513-a3ad90b407e2","content":"I don't have a skill for **analyzing** .dmp files — the available `dump-collect` skill is only for *capturing* dumps, not post-mortem investigation.\n\nHere's how you can analyze your dump:\n\n### Recommended Tools\n\n1. **`dotnet-dump analyze <file.dmp>`** (cross-platform)\n   ```bash\n   dotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n   dotnet-dump analyze your-crash.dmp\n   ```\n   Useful SOS commands inside the session:\n   - `clrstack` — managed call stack\n   - `pe` — print last exception\n   - `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n   - `threads` — list all threads\n\n2. **WinDbg** (Windows, most powerful)\n   - Load the dump, then `.loadby sos coreclr` and use `!analyze -v`\n\n3. **lldb + SOS** (Linux/macOS)\n   ```bash\n   dotnet-dump analyze your-crash.dmp\n   ```\n\n### Quick triage workflow\n```\n> dotnet-dump analyze crash.dmp\n$ pe              # show the exception that crashed the app\n$ clrstack        # show the managed stack of the current thread\n$ threads         # list threads to find the faulting one\n$ setthread <id>  # switch to a specific thread\n$ clrstack        # inspect that thread's stack\n```\n\nWould you like me to walk you through running any of these on your dump file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ed4f0db0-50f4-4084-87bc-d165701e740f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET application and wants to analyze it to find the root cause of a crash. Let me look at the available skills to see if any are relevant.\n\nLooking at the available skills:\n- `dump-collect` - This is for *collecting* crash dumps, not analyzing them. The description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\"\n- `dotnet-trace-collect` - For capturing diagnostic artifacts, not analyzing dumps\n- `android-tombstone-symbolication` - For Android tombstone files\n\n\n- `apple-crash-symbolication` - For Apple .ips crash logs\n\nNone of the available skills are designed for analyzing dump files, so I'll need to help the user directly with guidance on how to analyze their dump file.","outputTokens":567,"requestId":"A0C3:39E965:988652:BB8B39:6A0137F3"},"id":"496a0c47-7c96-4b23-95ac-f35932717ba6","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:59:29.876Z","parentId":"3465fd41-c345-4229-8e80-f87235281e9a"}
